What Azure storage method allows you to take a “point-in-time” version of your blob storage account,
and supports both managed and unmanaged disks?
ans is Snapshots
A blob snapshot is a read-only version of a blob that is captured at a point in time
Once a snapshot has been created, it can be read, copied, or deleted, but not modified
Snapshots provide a way to back up a blob as it appears at a moment in time
With the REST version 2015-07-08 and above,

